Ah, William, any papers yet?

61
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:23,260
-送报员迟到了  -见怪不怪
- They're late. - They certainly are.

62
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:27,350
把板子准备好  报纸一来就可以熨了
Get the board out so you can do them as soon as they're here.

63
00:04:31,770 --> 00:04:32,700
书房收拾妥当了吗
Is the library tidy?

64
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:34,270
收拾好了  休斯太太
Yes, Mrs Hughes.

65
00:04:34,350 --> 00:04:38,360
很好  今天要彻底打扫餐厅
Good. I want the dining room given a proper going over today.

66
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:41,280
他们用完早餐  你们就开始
You can do it when they've finished their breakfast.

67
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:43,110
天哪  傻丫头
Oh, heavens, girl!

68
00:04:43,650 --> 00:04:46,700
你是要生火  又不是钻木取火
You're building a fire, not inventing it.

69
00:04:46,820 --> 00:04:47,960
还剩几个了
How many have you done?

70
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,950
主人下楼前最后一个了
This is me last till they come downstairs.

71
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,120
很好
Very well.

72
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:55,000
赶紧回厨房  免得被人瞧见
Now, get back down to the kitchens before anyone sees you.

73
00:05:28,710 --> 00:05:31,460
-他们起来了  -片刻不得消停
- And they're off. - No rest for the wicked.

74
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:33,630
是玛丽小姐  茶盘备好了吗
Lady Mary. Are the tea trays ready?

75
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:35,050
都准备好了  帕特莫太太
All ready, Mrs Patmore.

76
00:05:35,170 --> 00:05:37,220
就等水开了
If the water's boiled.

77
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:38,720
你能帮忙把另两个端上去吗
Could you give us a hand to take the other two up?

78
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:40,380
我还要服侍夫人呢
I've got her ladyship's to carry.

79
00:05:40,470 --> 00:05:41,800
-我来吧  -后门有人
- I'll help. - Back door.

80
00:05:41,890 --> 00:05:43,970
报纸终于来了  威廉
The papers, at last. William!

81
00:05:45,810 --> 00:05:47,640
-你迟到了  -是  我知道  但是
- You're late. - Yeah, I know, but...

82
00:05:47,730 --> 00:05:50,140
-但是什么  -你看了就知道了
- But what? - You'll see.

83
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:59,490
先熨《泰晤士报》  他早餐时只读这份
Do The Times first, he only reads that at breakfast.

84
00:05:59,570 --> 00:06:01,320
再是夫人的《每日见闻报》
And the Sketch for her ladyship.

85
00:06:01,410 --> 00:06:04,530
其他的等会儿再说  如果需要的话
You can manage the others later, if need be.

86
00:06:11,420 --> 00:06:14,340
-为什么还要熨报纸  -关你什么事
- Why are their papers ironed? - What's it to you?

87
00:06:14,420 --> 00:06:15,840
为了让油墨干透  傻丫头
To dry the ink, silly.

88
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:18,920
怎能让老爷的手弄得和你一样脏呢
We wouldn't want his lordship's hands to be as black as yours.

89
00:06:22,590 --> 00:06:25,600
卡森先生  我想你得看看这个
Mr Carson, I think you ought to see this.

90
00:06:31,060 --> 00:06:33,860
-简直不敢相信  -我也是
- I can't make myself believe it. - Me neither.

91
00:06:33,940 --> 00:06:36,440
-老爷更衣完毕  -威廉
- His lordship's dressed. - William!

92
00:06:36,940 --> 00:06:39,360
别聊天了  把这盘鱼蛋烩饭端上去
Will you stop talking and take this kedgeree up.

93
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,940
小心下面还烧着火呢
And mind the burners are still lit.

94
00:06:40,940 --> 00:06:43,110
好的  帕特莫太太
Yes, Mrs Patmore.

95
00:06:43,700 --> 00:06:46,120
-这是真的吗  -恐怕是的
- Is it really true? - Afraid so.

96
00:06:46,620 --> 00:06:48,700
世事无常啊
Nothing in life is sure.

97
00:07:12,980 --> 00:07:13,850
早安  卡森  
Good morning, Carson.

98
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:16,310
早安  老爷
Good morning, my lord.

99
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:18,230
他们所言当真  
Is it true what they're saying?

100
00:07:18,230 --> 00:07:19,980
我想是的  老爷
I believe so, my lord.

101
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:22,070
恐怕船上还有我们认识的人
I'm afraid we'll know some people on it.

102
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:24,910
幸存者的名单还没公布吧
I don't suppose there are any lists of survivors yet?

103
00:07:24,990 --> 00:07:28,240
据我所知大多数女士被及时救出了
I understand most of the ladies were taken off in time.

104
00:07:28,330 --> 00:07:31,000
你是说头等舱的女宾吧
You mean the ladies in first class?

105
00:07:32,330 --> 00:07:35,120
上帝保佑那些下等舱的可怜人儿
God help the poor devils below decks.

106
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,340
死后能得以超度
On their way to a better life.

107
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:44,510
真是灭顶之灾啊
What a tragedy.

108
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:51,990
安娜告诉我的时候
When Anna told me,

109
00:07:51,990 --> 00:07:53,600
我还以为她说梦话呢
I thought she must have dreamt it.

110
00:07:53,690 --> 00:07:55,020
船上有熟人吗
Do we know anyone on board?

111
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:57,270
你妈妈认识阿斯特一家  至少认识他本人
Your mother knows the Astors, at least she knows him.

112
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:59,610
我们上个月还和罗斯小姐共进晚餐
We dined with Lady Rothes last month.

113
00:07:59,690 --> 00:08:01,360
势必还有其他熟人
There are bound to be others.

114
00:08:01,490 --> 00:08:04,200
我以为它永不沉没呢
I thought it was supposed to be unsinkable.

115
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:06,780
没有高不可攀的山峰
Every mountain is unclimbable until someone climbs it,

116
00:08:06,870 --> 00:08:09,990
也没有永不翻沉的船
so every ship is unsinkable until it sinks.

117
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:13,120
-早安  爸爸  -早  那是什么
- Good morning, Papa. - Good morning. What's that?

118
00:08:13,210 --> 00:08:15,290
刚到的  电报
Just arrived. Telegram.

119
00:08:37,270 --> 00:08:38,810
-夫人醒了吗  -醒了  老爷
- Is her ladyship awake? - Yes, my lord.

120
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:41,070
-我这就去把早餐端来  -谢了
- I'm just going to take in her breakfast. - Thank you.

121
00:08:41,190 --> 00:08:43,150
谁啊
Hello.

122
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,860
我能进来吗
May I come in?

123
00:08:47,450 --> 00:08:49,370
简直太不幸了
Isn't this terrible?

124
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:54,620
一想起露西·罗斯出发有多兴奋
When you think how excited Lucy Rothes was at the prospect.

125
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:57,290
真是惨到无以言表
It's too awful for any words.

126
00:08:58,250 --> 00:09:00,250
阿斯特逃过一劫了吗
Did J.J. Astor get off?

127
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:03,420
他的新婚妻子肯定获救了
Of course that new wife of his is bound to have been rescued.

128
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:05,760
我收到了乔治·莫里发来的电报
I've had a telegram from George Murray.

129
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:09,090
-他有位合伙人在纽约  -怎么了
- One of his partners is in New York. - Yes?

130
00:09:09,430 --> 00:09:11,800
詹姆斯和帕特里克好像也在船上
It seems James and Patrick were on board.

131
00:09:11,930 --> 00:09:15,020
什么  怎么可能  他们要五月才出发
What? They can't have been. They weren't going over until May.

132
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:16,880
那就是计划有变
Then they changed their plans.

133
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:19,310
他们的确在乘客名单上
They're on the passenger list.

134
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:22,520
谢谢  奥布瑞恩  先就这样吧
Thank you, O'Brien. That'll be all for the moment.

135
00:09:22,610 --> 00:09:25,070
但他们肯定获救了吧
But surely they were picked up?

136
00:09:28,410 --> 00:09:30,610
-不尽其然  -什么
- Doesn't look like it. - What?

137
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,950
一个都没救上来吗
Neither of them?

138
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:38,500
你得告诉玛丽
You must tell Mary.

139
00:09:39,790 --> 00:09:42,840
只有你亲口告诉她才行
She can't hear about it from anyone else.

140
00:09:53,310 --> 00:09:55,640
两个都没被救上来  他是这么说的
Neither of them were picked up, that's what he said.

141
00:09:55,770 --> 00:09:57,420
卡劳利先生和帕特里克少爷吗
Mr Crawley and Mr Patrick?

142
00:09:57,420 --> 00:09:58,850
他是这么说的
That's what he said.

143
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:01,520
夫人惊得面色煞白
Her ladyship was the colour of this cloth.

144
00:10:01,650 --> 00:10:04,150
如果真是这样  那就太可惜了
Well, it's a terrible shame if it's true.

145
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:07,360
怎一个可惜了得  这下麻烦大了
It's worse than a shame, it's a complication.

146
00:10:08,610 --> 00:10:11,030
-此话怎讲  -你说呢
- What do you mean? - What do you think?

147
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,980
卡劳利先生是老爷的堂兄
Mr Crawley was his lordship's cousin

148
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:14,580
也是爵位继承人
and heir to the title.

149
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:16,540
我以为玛丽小姐才是继承人
I thought Lady Mary was the heir.

150
00:10:16,660 --> 00:10:17,800
她是个女孩  傻丫头
She's a girl, stupid.

151
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:19,410
女孩不能做继承人
Girls can't inherit.

152
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:21,190
但现在卡劳利先生已故
But now Mr Crawley's dead

153
00:10:21,190 --> 00:10:23,000
而帕特里克少爷又是他的独子
and Mr Patrick was his only son.

154
00:10:23,130 --> 00:10:26,670
-这下如何是好  -真是太可怕了
- So, what happens next? - It's a dreadful thing.

155
00:10:28,130 --> 00:10:29,340
您好
Hello.

156
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:34,180
我一直等在后门  却一直没人应门
I've been waiting at the back door. I knocked, but no one came.

157
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:36,010
那你就推门而入了
So you pushed in?

158
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:38,770
我叫约翰·贝茨  是新来的男仆
I'm John Bates, the new valet.

159
00:10:38,850 --> 00:10:41,190
-新来的男仆  -没错
- The new valet? - That's right.

160
00:10:43,730 --> 00:10:46,150
-你来得真早  -搭清晨的车过来的
- You're early. - Came on the milk train.

161
00:10:46,230 --> 00:10:50,490
想用白天的时间熟悉环境  今晚上任
Thought I'd use the day to get to know the place, start tonight.

162
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:53,700
我是安娜  女仆领班
I'm Anna, the head housemaid.

163
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:56,160
您好
How do you do?

164
00:10:57,240 --> 00:11:00,250
我是奥布瑞恩小姐  夫人的贴身侍女
And I'm Miss O'Brien, her ladyship's maid.

165
00:11:02,210 --> 00:11:04,540
随我们来
You better come along with us.

166
00:11:14,010 --> 00:11:16,070
但你要怎么应付得过来
But how can you manage?

167
00:11:16,070 --> 00:11:17,640
不必担心  我自能应对
Don't worry about that, I can manage.

168
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:21,060
-我们可都有活在身  -我能行
- Because we've all got our own work to do. - I can manage.

169
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:22,190
好了  休斯太太
All right, Mrs Hughes,

170
00:11:22,190 --> 00:11:23,690
我来负责这里  谢谢
I'll take over. Thank you.

171
00:11:23,770 --> 00:11:27,110
早上好  贝茨先生  欢迎
Good morning, Mr Bates. Welcome.

172
00:11:27,730 --> 00:11:31,070
-愿你旅途一切顺利  -顺利  谢谢
- I hope your journey was satisfactory. - It was fine. Thank you.

173
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:34,280
我是唐顿庄园的管家  我叫卡森
I am the butler of Downton. My name is Carson.

174
00:11:34,410 --> 00:11:35,780
您好  卡森先生
How do you do, Mr Carson?

175
00:11:35,910 --> 00:11:37,990
这位是托马斯  第一男仆
This is Thomas, first footman.

176
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:39,730
自沃特森先生走后  老爷的起居
He's been looking after his lordship

177
00:11:39,730 --> 00:11:41,290
一直由他负责
since Mr Watson left.

178
00:11:41,410 --> 00:11:44,290
这下终于能回归正轨了  对吧  托马斯
It'll be a relief to get back to normal, won't it, Thomas?

179
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:48,790
贝茨先生的房间都安排妥当了吧
I assume that everything is ready for Mr Bates' arrival?

