00:21:26,610 --> 00:21:28,420
幸运的卡劳利家成员有什么消息
about the lucky Mr Crawley?

352
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,170
希望不算太糟
Nothing too terrible, I hope.

353
00:21:30,250 --> 00:21:32,230
我只做了一点调查
I've only made a few inquiries,

354
00:21:32,230 --> 00:21:34,960
不过没有什么需要您担心的
but no, there's not much to alarm you.

355
00:21:35,050 --> 00:21:36,990
马修·卡劳利是一名律师
Matthew Crawley is a solicitor

356
00:21:36,990 --> 00:21:38,050
在曼彻斯特工作
based in Manchester.

357
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:39,590
曼彻斯特
Manchester?

358
00:21:40,180 --> 00:21:42,720
他的专长是公司法
His special field is company law.

359
00:21:43,970 --> 00:21:46,180
母亲健在  和他住在一起
His mother is alive and he lives with her.

360
00:21:46,270 --> 00:21:49,190
父亲已过世  生前是医生
His father obviously is not. He was a doctor.

361
00:21:49,270 --> 00:21:50,560
我知道了
I know.

362
00:21:51,060 --> 00:21:52,130
这真够古怪的
It does seem odd

363
00:21:52,130 --> 00:21:54,320
我的远房堂兄竟做了医生
that my third cousin should be a doctor.

364
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:56,820
医生也差不到哪里去
There are worse professions.

365
00:21:57,700 --> 00:21:58,990
的确如此
Indeed.

366
00:22:07,210 --> 00:22:08,070
帮个忙  
Do me a favour.

367
00:22:08,070 --> 00:22:09,620
这个应该撒在鸡肉上
This is supposed to be sprinkled on the chicken.

368
00:22:09,790 --> 00:22:11,090
不是还有菜要端吗
But isn't there more to go up?

369
00:22:11,090 --> 00:22:12,580
求你了  用不了几分钟
Oh, please, it won't take a moment.

370
00:22:12,670 --> 00:22:14,170
-好吧  交给我  -好的
- Go on then, give it here.  - Okay.

371
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:18,470
我们该谈谈限定继承权的事情
We ought to talk about the business of the entail.

372
00:22:18,550 --> 00:22:20,300
如你所知  你百年之后
As you know, on your death,

373
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:23,010
承袭爵位者将继承这一切
the heir to the title inherits everything,

374
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:26,810
除了留给孤儿寡母的那点遗产
except for the sums set aside for your daughters and your widow.

375
00:22:26,890 --> 00:22:28,020
是的
Yes.

376
00:22:28,310 --> 00:22:30,190
根据夫人的婚姻协议
Owing to the terms of her settlement,

377
00:22:30,270 --> 00:22:33,690
这也包括她的那部分财产
this will include the bulk of your wife's fortune.

378
00:22:33,770 --> 00:22:36,400
沉船之后这成了我们
It has been our sole topic of conversation

379
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,610
唯一的话题
since the day the ship went down.

380
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:41,490
尽管对格兰瑟姆夫人非常不公
Of course it must seem horribly unjust to Lady Grantham,

381
00:22:41,570 --> 00:22:43,240
可法律规定如此
but that is how the law stands.

382
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:46,120
真没有办法帮她留份财产吗
Is there really no way to detach her money from the estate?

383
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:48,570
连我都觉得这很荒谬
Even to me, it seems absurd.

384
00:22:48,660 --> 00:22:51,310
令尊坚持要这么做
Your father tied the knots pretty tight.

385
00:22:51,310 --> 00:22:53,080
没有余地变通
I'd say it's unbreakable.

386
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:54,450
我懂了
I see.

387
00:22:55,590 --> 00:22:59,010
伊迪丝  何必这么入戏呢
Really, Edith, do you have to put on such an exhibition?

388
00:22:59,010 --> 00:23:00,620
她是真伤心
She's not.

389
00:23:00,930 --> 00:23:03,760
要和他订婚的不是你  是我
I was supposed to be engaged to him, for heaven's sake, not you.

390
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:06,210
我都没这么失态
And I can control myself.

391
00:23:06,260 --> 00:23:08,670
那你就该羞愧
Then you should be ashamed.

392
00:23:09,430 --> 00:23:13,180
这碗蛋怎么还没送上去
Oh, and don't tell me you've not sent up the egg yet.

393
00:23:16,230 --> 00:23:18,610
噢上帝  帮帮我  求你了帮帮我
Oh, God, help me! Please, God, help me!

394
00:23:18,610 --> 00:23:20,110
怎么回事
Well, what on earth's the matter?

395
00:23:20,110 --> 00:23:22,230
赶快去楼上餐厅找威廉
Just run upstairs to the dining room and find William.

396
00:23:22,230 --> 00:23:23,990
-求你了  -我现在没空
- I beg you.  - I can't do that now.

397
00:23:23,990 --> 00:23:24,660
求你帮帮忙
You've got to.

398
00:23:24,660 --> 00:23:26,580
-不然我死定了  -什么
- I'll be hanged if you don't.  - What?

399
00:23:26,580 --> 00:23:28,240
黛西  是你吗
Daisy, is that you?

400
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,500
是洒在鸡肉沙拉上
Is it the chicken in a sauce

401
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:31,410
还是橘片白切鸡上
or the plain chicken with sliced oranges?

402
00:23:31,410 --> 00:23:36,580
感谢万能慈悲的主  谢谢你
Oh, thank you, blessed and merciful Lord! Thank you.

403
00:23:37,170 --> 00:23:38,670
洒在鸡丝沙拉上
It's the chicken in the sauce.

404
00:23:38,670 --> 00:23:43,170
我以后要多做善事  我发誓
I'll never do anything sinful again, I swear it. Not till I die.

405
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:49,680
莫里先生  幸会  快请进
Mr Murray, how lovely to see you. Do come in.

406
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:51,580
多谢盛情  格兰瑟姆夫人
You're very kind, Lady Grantham,

407
00:23:51,580 --> 00:23:52,730
但我要赶回伦敦
but I must get back to London.

408
00:23:52,730 --> 00:23:54,580
不留下吃午饭了吗
But you'll stay for luncheon?

409
00:23:54,580 --> 00:23:57,230
没这个福气了  我在火车上吃
Thank you, but no, I'll eat on the train.

410
00:23:57,230 --> 00:23:59,220
可否劳驾您
In fact, if you'd be so good

411
00:23:59,220 --> 00:24:01,690
派车送我过去
as to ask for the motor be brought round?

412
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:04,950
下午不再谈谈了吗
But didn't you want the afternoon to talk things through?

413
00:24:04,950 --> 00:24:06,760
已经谈得差不多了
I think we've said everything we have to say,

414
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:08,200
您说对吗  阁下
haven't we, my lord?

415
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:10,040
目前是差不多了
For the time being, yes.

416
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:11,870
谢谢你  莫里
Thank you, Murray.

417
00:24:11,870 --> 00:24:13,700
你的建议我会考虑
You've given me a good deal to think about.

418
00:24:17,340 --> 00:24:20,300
玛丽  请大家进餐厅
Mary, try to get everyone into the dining room.

419
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:23,790
伊迪丝  请敏特里老爷坐下
Edith, make sure old Lord Minterne sits down.

420
00:24:30,350 --> 00:24:33,630
-都走了吗  -感谢上帝  都走了
- They've all gone?  - They have, thank the Lord.

421
00:24:34,270 --> 00:24:37,520
-律师呢  -他头一个走
- Oh, what about the lawyer?  - Oh, he was the first away.

422
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:39,610
连午饭都没吃
Didn't even stay for the luncheon.

423
00:24:39,610 --> 00:24:42,190
怎么不早说呢
I wish they'd make their minds up.

424
00:24:42,190 --> 00:24:44,490
格温连蓝屋的床单都铺了
Gwen's put clean sheets on the Blue Room bed.

425
00:24:44,490 --> 00:24:46,820
现在又得收起来
Now she'll just have to strip it again.

426
00:24:46,820 --> 00:24:49,180
留给以后的客人不行吗
Can't you leave it for the next guest?

427
00:24:49,180 --> 00:24:51,150
除非你不告状
Well, only if you don't tell.

428
00:24:54,330 --> 00:24:57,660
尘埃落定了吗
So, has it all been settled?

429
00:24:57,790 --> 00:25:00,590
哪儿都没落定呢
No. I don't know if anything's been settled.

430
00:25:00,590 --> 00:25:04,340
曼城确实有位继承人
There's a fellow in Manchester with claims to the title,

431
00:25:04,340 --> 00:25:07,880
但离确定还早着呢
I gather, but it's all a long way from settled.

432
00:25:07,930 --> 00:25:09,580
你可别往心里去
You mustn't take it personally.

433
00:25:09,580 --> 00:25:11,760
不  我确实很担心  休斯太太
No, I do take it personally, Mrs. Hughes.

434
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:14,690
我不忍心眼睁睁
I can't stand by and watch our family

435
00:25:14,690 --> 00:25:16,930
看着亲人无端失去财产
threatened with a loss of all they hold dear.

436
00:25:17,310 --> 00:25:18,950
他们不算我们亲人吧
They are not our family.

437
00:25:18,950 --> 00:25:21,680
他们是我唯一的亲人
Well, they're all the family I've got.

438
00:25:26,490 --> 00:25:28,520
抱歉  我失态了
I beg your pardon.

439
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:38,030
你可曾想过另一种生活吗
Do you ever wish you'd gone another way?

440
00:25:43,050 --> 00:25:45,450
开店做工  
Worked in a shop or a factory?

441
00:25:45,450 --> 00:25:47,460
娶妻生子吗
Had a wife and children?

442
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:49,790
你后悔吗
Do you?

443
00:25:52,100 --> 00:25:55,130
不知道  可能有点
I don't know. Maybe.

444
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:57,090
有时候挺后悔
Sometimes.

445
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:01,350
威廉在书房摆好茶了
William's laid tea in the library,

446
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:03,190
但夫人还没下楼
but Her Ladyship hasn't come down.

447
00:26:03,190 --> 00:26:07,070
她累了  端上去送进房吧
Oh, she'll be tired. Take a tray up to her bedroom.

448
00:26:07,070 --> 00:26:09,940
-托马斯回来了吗  -还没有  卡森先生
- Is Thomas back? - Not yet, Mr. Carson.

449
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:15,410
他请了假去村里逛逛
He asked if he could run down the village,

450
00:26:15,410 --> 00:26:17,030
我何必拦着
I didn't see why not.

451
00:26:43,190 --> 00:26:44,980
太不公平了
It's iniquitous.

452
00:26:44,980 --> 00:26:47,160
您平白没了财产
They can't expect you to sit by silent

453
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:49,110
还得故作镇定
as your fortune is stolen away.

454
00:26:49,110 --> 00:26:50,240
又能怎样
Can't they?

455
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:53,360
老爷不会不管的
His Lordship would never let it happen.

456
00:26:53,820 --> 00:26:56,110
贝茨干得怎么样
How's Bates working out?

457
00:26:56,490 --> 00:26:59,200
我不敢评论
Well, I don't like to say.

458
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:02,770
他腿脚不方便
Only it seems unkind to criticise a man

459
00:27:02,770 --> 00:27:05,450
我不该多嘴的
for an affliction, my lady.

460
00:27:06,460 --> 00:27:09,330
哪怕他不能胜任
Even if it means he can't do his job.

461
00:27:16,140 --> 00:27:18,380
做得还习惯吗
How are you settling in?

462
00:27:18,810 --> 00:27:22,890
若老爷没有异议  我觉得还不错
Very well, I think. Unless your Lordship feels differently.

463
00:27:22,980 --> 00:27:24,440
没什么不顺心的吗
No complaints?

464
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:26,680
即使有  也该先跟卡森先生说
If I had any, I should take them to Mr. Carson,

465
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:27,720
而不是找老爷您
my Lord, not you.

466
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:31,310
那倒是
You're probably right.

467
00:27:32,030 --> 00:27:34,210
这上楼下楼的
And the house hasn't worn you out

468
00:27:34,210 --> 00:27:36,160
你吃得消吗
with the endless stairs and everything?

469
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:40,030
我喜欢这房子  老爷  喜欢在这干活
I like the house, my Lord. I like it as a place to work.

470
00:27:41,710 --> 00:27:45,070
-那是怎么回事  -旧伤罢了
- What happened?  - Oh, it's only the old wound.

471
00:27:45,670 --> 00:27:47,880
退伍后我遇上点麻烦
After I left the army, I had a spot of bother

472
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:49,660
后来解决了
and just when I got through that

473
00:27:49,660 --> 00:27:53,080
一年前这膝盖开始不听使唤
about a year ago my knee started playing up.

474
00:27:53,220 --> 00:27:55,360
里面有块弹片移了位
A bit of shrapnel got left in or something and it moved,

475
00:27:55,360 --> 00:27:56,850
不过不碍事
but it's fine.

476
00:27:56,850 --> 00:27:58,220
没问题
It's not a problem.

477
00:27:58,220 --> 00:28:01,720
要有问题了  就跟我说
And you'd let me know if you felt it was all too much for you?

478
00:28:01,730 --> 00:28:04,050
是  不会有问题的
I would. But it won't be.

479
00:28:05,900 --> 00:28:07,390
托马斯
Thomas.

480
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:11,230
-你去哪了  -村子里
- And where have you been?  - The village.

481
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:13,710
发电报去了  若非打听不可
To send a telegram, if you must know.

482
00:28:13,710 --> 00:28:15,730
随便打听嘛
Pardon me for living.

483
00:28:21,330 --> 00:28:24,070
莫里没呆多久
Well, Murray didn't stay long.

484
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:30,750
-夫人知道结果吗  -不知道
- Does Her Ladyship know how they left it?  - No.

485
00:28:30,750 --> 00:28:34,340
他们从教堂回来  路上就谈完了
They talked it all through on the way back from the church.

486
00:28:34,340 --> 00:28:36,720
我要还跟老爷  早探出消息了
If I was still his valet, I'd get it out of him.

487
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:39,960
-贝茨的嘴严着呢  -没错
- Bates won't say a word.  - He will not.

488
00:28:41,350 --> 00:28:44,720
十镑  我赌他是主子的眼线
I bet you a tenner he's a spy in the other direction.

489
00:28:45,730 --> 00:28:47,760
我想跟着老爷
I wanted that job.

490
00:28:47,900 --> 00:28:49,730
我可是他的得力助手
We were all right together, His Lordship and me.

491
00:28:49,730 --> 00:28:51,730
那等贝茨走了
Then be sure to get your foot in the door

492
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:53,860
你就想办法跟紧老爷
when Bates is gone.

493
00:28:53,860 --> 00:28:57,570
光说他暗地里嚼舌根可赶不走他
You can't get rid of him just because he talks behind our backs.

494
00:28:57,570 --> 00:29:00,110
东方不亮西方亮  办法多的是
There's more than one way to skin a cat.

495
00:29:01,620 --> 00:29:05,410
-夫人没听懂吧  -说得很明白了
- Perhaps she misunderstood.  - No, it was quite plain.

496
00:29:05,620 --> 00:29:08,290
奥布瑞恩明说了  贝茨伺候不好老爷
O'Brien told her Bates can't do the job properly.

497
00:29:08,290 --> 00:29:09,920
怎么偏请了他呢
Why was he taken on?

498
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:13,210
布尔战争时  他给老爷当过勤务兵
He was Lord Grantham's batman when he was fighting the Boers.

499
00:29:13,210 --> 00:29:15,470
我知道  那也犯不着
I know that, but even so.

500
00:29:15,470 --> 00:29:17,470
-我觉得定有原因  -什么原因
- I think it's romantic.  - I don't.

501
00:29:17,470 --> 00:29:19,640
一个瘸子怎么当贴身侍从呢
How can a valet do his work if he's lame?

502
00:29:19,640 --> 00:29:21,670
倒不是特别瘸
He's not very lame.

503
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:24,770
好了  小姐还有吩咐吗
There. Anything else before I go down?

504
00:29:24,770 --> 00:29:27,140
没了  下去吧
No, that's it. Thank you.

505
00:29:35,650 --> 00:29:37,690
一身黑真难看
Oh, I hate black.

506
00:29:37,820 --> 00:29:39,320
又不用穿很久
It's not for long.

507
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:42,330
妈妈说下个月就改半丧
Mama says we can go into half-mourning next month.

508
00:29:42,330 --> 00:29:43,950
到九月就不用穿黑了
And back to colours by September.

509
00:29:43,950 --> 00:29:47,700
-死了堂兄而已  何必呢  -不是未婚夫吗
- Still seems a lot for a cousin.  - But not a fiance?

510
00:29:51,500 --> 00:29:54,370
-不算未婚夫吧  -真的吗
- He wasn't really a fiance.  - No?

511
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:58,340
都要结婚了  还不是未婚夫
I thought that was what you call a man you're going to marry.

512
00:29:58,340 --> 00:30:01,510
实在没得选了我才会嫁给他
I was only going to marry him if nothing better turned up.

513
00:30:01,510 --> 00:30:04,430
-玛丽  别这么说  -怕什么
- Mary, what a horrid thing to say.  - Don't worry.

514
00:30:04,430 --> 00:30:06,880
想嫁他的是伊迪丝  对吧
Edith would have taken him, wouldn't you?

515
00:30:06,930 --> 00:30:09,550
是  我想嫁他
Yes, I'd have taken him.

516
00:30:10,310 --> 00:30:14,720
要不是你  我早嫁给他了
If you'd given me the chance, I'd have taken him like a shot.

517
00:30:15,780 --> 00:30:18,530
这实在行不通  卡森先生
I just think you should know it's not working, Mr. Carson.

518
00:30:18,530 --> 00:30:21,030
贝茨先生很懒散吗
Do you mean Mr. Bates is lazy?

519
00:30:21,030 --> 00:30:25,230
不是懒散  是干不了重活
Not lazy, exactly. But he just can't carry.

520
00:30:25,370 --> 00:30:27,000
他连老爷的箱子都差点提不动
He can hardly manage His Lordship's cases.

521
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,030
去伦敦参加追思会的那次   
You saw how it was when they went up

522
00:30:28,030 --> 00:30:29,870
您也看见了
to London for the memorial.

523
00:30:29,870 --> 00:30:31,500
他也没法帮客人拿行李
He can't help with the guests' luggage neither.

524
00:30:31,500 --> 00:30:33,670
更别说伺候用餐了
And as for waiting at table, we can forget that.

525
00:30:33,670 --> 00:30:35,360
你想让我怎么样呢
And what do you want me to do?

526
