若需额外男仆时
That when an extra footman is required,

865
00:49:22,500 --> 00:49:23,960
他的工钱从我工资里扣
the cost could come out of my wages.

866
00:49:24,260 --> 00:49:26,590
不行  我决不允许
Absolutely not. I couldn't possibly allow that.

867
00:49:26,680 --> 00:49:29,770
可我很想留下来  老爷  
Because I am very eager to stay, my lord.

868
00:49:29,770 --> 00:49:30,720
真的很想
Very eager, indeed.

869
00:49:32,810 --> 00:49:36,390
我知道  我也很希望你能留下来
I know you are. And I was eager that this should work.

870
00:49:40,020 --> 00:49:44,070
像我这样的很难再找到工作了
You see, it is unlikely that I should find another position.

871
00:49:44,360 --> 00:49:47,030
房子小些  责任轻些的工作肯定行
But surely in a smaller house, where less is expected of you.

872
00:49:47,240 --> 00:49:48,700
也不太可能
It's not likely.

873
00:49:50,070 --> 00:49:51,910
在你找到工作前我会帮助你
I mean to help until you find something.

874
00:49:51,990 --> 00:49:54,200
我不能要您的钱  老爷
I couldn't take your money, my lord.

875
00:49:54,200 --> 00:49:56,830
除非那是我的劳动所得
I can take wages for a job done. That's all.

876
00:50:04,130 --> 00:50:06,760
好吧  老爷  我马上走
Very good, my lord. I'll go at once.

877
00:50:07,130 --> 00:50:08,730
不必急着今晚走
There's no need to rush out into the night.

878
00:50:08,730 --> 00:50:11,600
搭明早九点的火车去伦敦吧
Take the London train tomorrow. It leaves at 9:00.

879
00:50:11,680 --> 00:50:14,970
我会多给你一个月的工资  千万收下
You'll have a month's wages, too. That I insist on.

880
00:50:21,520 --> 00:50:23,120
我也不想这样  贝茨
It's a bloody business, Bates,

881
00:50:23,120 --> 00:50:25,820
实在是别无他法
but I can't see any way around it.

882
00:50:26,030 --> 00:50:28,360
我理解  老爷
I quite understand, my lord.

883
00:50:37,040 --> 00:50:40,670
看来今晚是女士之夜了  公爵
I'm afraid we're rather a female party tonight, Duke.

884
00:50:41,710 --> 00:50:42,960
但是你也知道
But you know what it's

885
00:50:42,960 --> 00:50:45,590
乡下总是女多男少
like trying to balance numbers in the country.

886
00:50:45,670 --> 00:50:48,340
单身汉在这里可是众星捧月
A single man outranks the Holy Grail.

887
00:50:50,010 --> 00:50:53,550
不  能与您一家共进晚餐实在荣幸之至
No, I'm terribly flattered to be dining en famille.

888
00:50:54,180 --> 00:50:57,600
下午您和玛丽在小阁楼做什么呢
What were you and Mary doing in the attics this afternoon?

889
00:50:58,680 --> 00:51:02,730
我想玛丽只是带公爵到处看看而已  对吧
I expect Mary was just showing the Duke the house. Weren't you?

890
00:51:05,360 --> 00:51:08,650
-您是学建筑的吗  -没错
- Are you a student of architecture? - Mmm, absolutely.

891
00:51:08,740 --> 00:51:11,910
那我诚挚希望您能光临寒舍
Then I do hope you'll come and inspect my little cottage.

892
00:51:12,240 --> 00:51:15,720
那是雷恩大师为第一任伯爵的妹妹设计建造的
It was designed by Wren for the first earl's sister.

893
00:51:15,720 --> 00:51:17,200
小阁楼
The attics?

894
00:51:17,290 --> 00:51:21,040
没错  玛丽带着公爵上了小阁楼
Yes. Mary took the Duke up to the attics.

895
00:51:21,420 --> 00:51:23,080
去那做什么
Whatever for?

896
00:51:23,540 --> 00:51:25,130
亲爱的  怎么回事
Why was this, dear?

897
00:51:25,210 --> 00:51:27,000
我们就是随处参观
We were just looking around.

898
00:51:27,090 --> 00:51:31,260
参观  仆人的房间有什么可看的
Looking around? What is there to look at but servants' rooms?

899
00:51:31,550 --> 00:51:33,220
到底是为什么呢
What was the real reason, hmm?

900
00:51:33,300 --> 00:51:36,510
别絮絮叨叨的  伊迪丝
Don't be such a chatterbox, Edith.

901
00:51:38,220 --> 00:51:40,180
我看大家都吃完了
I think we'll go through.

902
00:51:40,270 --> 00:51:44,100
-我还是不懂  -少说几句行吗
- I still don't understand... - Will you hold your tongue!

903
00:51:53,780 --> 00:51:55,820
还要等多久  我快饿死了
How long do you think they'll be? I'm starving.

904
00:51:55,910 --> 00:51:57,250
夫人小姐们都安顿好了吗
Have you settled the ladies?

905
00:51:57,250 --> 00:51:58,490
是的  卡森管家
Yes, Mr Carson.

906
00:51:58,580 --> 00:52:01,120
那就不会太久了
Then it won't be long once they go through.

907
00:52:01,210 --> 00:52:03,370
你们觉得他会求婚吗
You think he'll speak out?

908
00:52:03,460 --> 00:52:06,250
想想看我们就要有个公爵夫人伺候了
Do you think we'll have a duchess to wait on? Imagine that.

909
00:52:06,340 --> 00:52:08,460
那也轮不到你来伺候
You won't be waiting on her, whatever happens.

910
00:52:08,550 --> 00:52:10,160
格兰瑟姆伯爵的长女和继承人
There is no reason why the eldest daughter

911
00:52:10,160 --> 00:52:11,780
成为公爵夫人
and heiress of the Earl of Grantham

912
00:52:11,780 --> 00:52:15,010
再合适不过了
should not wear a duchess's coronet with honour.

913
00:52:15,090 --> 00:52:18,390
继承人  已经决定了吗  卡森先生
Heiress, Mr Carson? Has it been decided?

914
00:52:18,910 --> 00:52:21,850
世间若还有公道  她理应继承
It will be, if there's any justice in the world.

915
00:52:21,930 --> 00:52:24,350
好吧  分晓不久便知
Well, we'll know soon enough.

916
00:52:25,400 --> 00:52:26,520
你在干什么  安娜
What are you doing, Anna?

917
00:52:26,610 --> 00:52:29,410
我想拿点吃的给贝茨先生
I thought I'd take something up to Mr Bates,

918
00:52:29,410 --> 00:52:31,900
他不舒服没下来吃饭
him not being well enough to come down.

919
00:52:32,280 --> 00:52:34,310
您不介意吧  休斯太太
You don't mind, do you, Mrs Hughes?

920
00:52:34,310 --> 00:52:36,320
我没意见  但仅此一次
I don't mind. Not this once.

921
00:52:36,410 --> 00:52:39,080
去吧  给他送吃的吧
No, take him whatever he might need.

922
00:52:40,040 --> 00:52:43,710
贝茨先生的离开与他的品性无关
Mr Bates is leaving without a stain on his character.

923
00:52:44,120 --> 00:52:47,250
我希望你们与他道别时注意分寸
I hope you all observe that in the manner of your parting.

924
00:52:47,340 --> 00:52:48,640
我不明白他为什么要走
Well, I don't see why he has to go.

925
00:52:48,640 --> 00:52:50,130
我不介意多做一些...
I don't mind doing a bit of extra work...

926
00:52:50,210 --> 00:52:52,050
这不是你能决定的
It's not up to you.

927
00:52:52,760 --> 00:52:54,970
让我来服侍老爷  卡森先生  行吗
I'll take care of his lordship. Shall I, Mr Carson?

928
00:52:55,050 --> 00:52:57,470
不行  你还得照顾公爵
Not while you're looking after the Duke, you won't.

929
00:52:57,550 --> 00:53:00,680
还是我自己来伺候吧
I'll see to his lordship myself.

930
00:53:31,960 --> 00:53:34,840
贝茨先生  你在吗
Mr Bates? Are you there?

931
00:53:51,770 --> 00:53:55,030
怕你饿着  我给你端了点吃的
I brought something up, in case you were hungry.

932
00:53:57,070 --> 00:53:58,950
你真好  谢谢
That's very kind.

933
00:54:10,540 --> 00:54:14,000
-很遗憾你要走了  -我会没事的
- I'm ever so sorry you're going. - I'll be all right.

934
00:54:16,550 --> 00:54:18,340
那是当然
Of course you will.

935
00:54:18,930 --> 00:54:21,850
以你的为人  总能找到容身之处
There's always a place for a man like you.

936
00:54:21,930 --> 00:54:25,140
没错  总会有办法的
Oh, yes. Something will turn up.

937
00:54:28,980 --> 00:54:31,350
安顿好了  记得告诉我们
Tell us when you're fixed.

938
00:54:31,810 --> 00:54:34,520
写封信来
Just... drop us a line.

939
00:54:36,150 --> 00:54:37,940
不然我会担心的
Else I'll worry.

940
00:54:38,780 --> 00:54:41,820
放心吧
Well, we can't have that.

941
00:55:01,390 --> 00:55:03,930
咱们该让仆人进来收拾了
We must go and let the servants get in here.

942
00:55:04,010 --> 00:55:06,540
若能再逗留片刻  我将不胜感激
I should be grateful if we could stay just a minute more.

943
00:55:06,540 --> 00:55:08,060
还有些事想请教
I have... I have something to ask you.

944
00:55:15,690 --> 00:55:18,610
对于您兄侄的遭遇  我深表哀悼
I was terribly sorry to hear about your cousins.

945
00:55:18,690 --> 00:55:20,110
这样
You said.

946
00:55:20,860 --> 00:55:22,350
-您认识他们  -不太熟
- Did you know them? - Not well.

947
00:55:22,350 --> 00:55:25,910
也就见过帕特里克·卡劳利几次
I used to see Patrick Crawley at the odd thing.

948
00:55:27,540 --> 00:55:31,000
府上遭受如此巨变肯定需要时间适应
I imagine it will mean some adjustments for you all.

949
00:55:33,540 --> 00:55:38,000
一夜之间  失去两位继承人  太可怕了
To lose two heirs in one night, it's terrible.

950
00:55:38,550 --> 00:55:41,010
-是啊  很可怕  -真不幸
- Indeed, it was terrible. - Awful.

951
00:55:45,970 --> 00:55:48,600
但话说回来  祸兮福所倚
But then again, it's an ill wind.

952
00:55:50,270 --> 00:55:54,100
至少现在玛丽小姐的未来不可限量
At least Lady Mary's prospects must have rather improved.

953
00:55:55,360 --> 00:55:56,820
是吗
Have they?

954
00:55:58,820 --> 00:56:00,400
不是吗
Haven't they?

955
00:56:01,030 --> 00:56:03,150
恕我直言
I will not be coy

956
00:56:03,240 --> 00:56:05,820
我不想假装没听出您的弦外之音
and pretend I do not understand your meaning,

957
00:56:05,910 --> 00:56:10,160
似乎您对我家的私事洞若观火
though you seem very informed on this family's private affairs.

958
00:56:10,910 --> 00:56:12,740
那您也该知道此事
But you ought perhaps to know

959
00:56:12,740 --> 00:56:15,170
我无意打破限定继承权
that I do not intend to fight the entail.

960
00:56:15,250 --> 00:56:17,210
毫无此意
Not any part of it.

961
00:56:18,750 --> 00:56:20,710
您不是说真的吧
You can't be serious.

962
00:56:21,920 --> 00:56:24,470
尽管艰难  但我确无此意
It pains me to say it, but I am.

963
00:56:29,010 --> 00:56:31,810
您要放弃所有家产吗
You'll give up your entire estate?

964
00:56:32,060 --> 00:56:35,850
将您夫人的财产也交给一个陌生人吗
Your wife's money into the bargain, to a perfect stranger?

965
00:56:36,020 --> 00:56:37,860
您都不反抗吗
You won't even put up a fight?

966
00:56:37,940 --> 00:56:39,920
我希望他是个完美的继承人
I hope he proves to be perfect,

967
00:56:39,920 --> 00:56:41,400
但我很怀疑
but I'd rather doubt it.

968
00:56:43,610 --> 00:56:45,530
拿这种事说笑  够古怪
Very odd thing to joke about.

969
00:56:45,610 --> 00:56:48,160
这场谈话  更古怪
No odder than this conversation.

970
00:56:49,950 --> 00:56:52,000
给你的答复如下
So, there you have it.

971
00:56:53,000 --> 00:56:54,830
留给玛丽的那部分财产依旧
But Mary will still have her settlement,

972
00:56:54,830 --> 00:56:56,290
您不会嫌少的
which you won't find ungenerous.

973
00:56:58,000 --> 00:57:01,420
-您说什么  -我的意思是
- I'm sorry? - I only meant that

974
00:57:02,050 --> 00:57:05,970
她嫁妆的价值相当可观
her portion, when she marries, will be more than respectable.

975
00:57:06,050 --> 00:57:09,300
-您会满意的  我保证  -天哪
- You'll be pleased, I promise you. - Oh, heavens.

976
00:57:09,390 --> 00:57:11,330
真希望  您没有会错我的意
I hope I haven't given the wrong impression.

977
00:57:11,330 --> 00:57:12,060
您心里清楚
You know very well...

978
00:57:12,140 --> 00:57:15,390
-我尊敬的格兰瑟姆伯爵  -别给我来这套
- My dear Lord Grantham... - Don't "My dear Lord Grantham" Me!

979
00:57:15,480 --> 00:57:18,730
此行的目的  您心知肚明
You knew what you were doing when you came here.

980
00:57:18,980 --> 00:57:21,360
您让玛丽以及我们所有人都以为
You encouraged Mary, all of us, into thinking...

981
00:57:21,440 --> 00:57:22,880
对不起  我来此
Forgive me, but I came

982
00:57:22,880 --> 00:57:25,700
只是为了表达我的哀悼以及友好
to express my sympathies and my friendship.

983
00:57:25,780 --> 00:57:27,200
别无他意
Nothing more.

984
00:57:29,070 --> 00:57:31,130
玛丽小姐是位迷人的女士
Lady Mary is a charming person.

985
00:57:31,130 --> 00:57:33,790
谁娶了她都很幸运
Whoever marries her will be a lucky man.

986
00:57:34,870 --> 00:57:37,250
但那不会是我
It will not, however, be me.

987
00:57:37,670 --> 00:57:41,630
懂了  那您留我在此  是要问我什么
I see, and what was it you asked me to stay behind to hear?

988
00:57:45,720 --> 00:57:47,340
我  我忘了
I... I forget.

989
00:58:01,940 --> 00:58:05,150
您不来客厅了吗
Well, aren't you coming into the drawing room?

990
00:58:05,490 --> 00:58:06,130
我累了
I'm... I'm tired.

991
00:58:06,130 --> 00:58:08,060
失陪
I think I'll just slip away.

992
00:58:08,060 --> 00:58:09,990
麻烦替我致歉
Please make my excuses.

993
00:58:10,570 --> 00:58:12,560
看来你今天累坏了
I'm afraid I've worn you out.

994
00:58:12,560 --> 00:58:13,740
明天我们就...
Tomorrow we can just...

995
00:58:13,830 --> 00:58:15,750
我明早就告辞
I'm leaving in the morning.

996
00:58:15,750 --> 00:58:17,040
晚安
Good night.

997
00:58:20,130 --> 00:58:22,380
麻烦你告诉那位男仆
Oh, you might tell that footman...

998
00:58:22,630 --> 00:58:26,130
-托马斯  -托马斯  告诉他我回房歇息了
- Thomas. - Thomas. You might tell him I've gone up.

999
00:58:44,110 --> 00:58:46,110
金龟婿没上钩吗
So he slipped the hook?

1000
00:58:48,280 --> 00:58:51,200
至少我没有坐以待毙
At least I'm not fishing with no bait.

1001
00:59:00,330 --> 00:59:02,290
难以置信
I don't believe that.

1002
00:59:03,000 --> 00:59:06,960
你爱信不信  他不会推翻限定继承权的
Well, believe what you like. He won't break the entail.

1003
00:59:08,590 --> 00:59:11,180
未知的堂弟将继承一切
The unknown cousin gets everything

1004
00:59:12,050 --> 00:59:14,890
玛丽分得的遗产还是那么多
and Mary's inheritance will be the same as it always was.

1005
00:59:14,970 --> 00:59:16,930
我怎么知道  那个律师来  我还以为
Oh, how was I to know? When the lawyer turned up, I thought...

1006
00:59:17,020 --> 00:59:20,270
你是没法知道  给我发电报是对的
You weren't to and you did the right thing to telegraph me.

1007
00:59:20,390 --> 00:59:23,560
-只是事情未能如愿  -那现在怎么办
- It's just not going to come off. - So what now?

1008
00:59:25,650 --> 00:59:28,610
你知道我的使命决不会变
Well, you know how I'm fixed.

1009
00:59:29,950 --> 00:59:31,680
我得娶一位继承人
I have to have an heiress,

1010
00:59:31,680 --> 00:59:34,490
为此奔赴纽约也在所不惜
if it means going to New York to find one.

1011
00:59:36,870 --> 00:59:38,490
那我怎么办
What about me?

1012
00:59:41,080 --> 00:59:42,340
你
You...

1013
00:59:43,410 --> 00:59:44,500
你祝我顺风就好
You will wish me well.

1014
00:59:45,090 --> 00:59:47,960
你说过  如果我想离开  你会给我找份工
You said you'd find me ajob if I wanted to leave.

1015
00:59:48,050 --> 00:59:49,510
你想离开吗
And do you?

1016
00:59:50,510 --> 00:59:51,830
我想当贴身侍从
I want to be a valet.

1017
00:59:51,830 --> 00:59:52,800
我受够了男仆的工作
I'm sick of being a footman.

1018
00:59:52,890 --> 00:59:55,510
托马斯  我不需要贴身侍从
Yeah, Thomas, I don't need a valet.

1019
00:59:57,640 --> 00:59:59,770
我以为你要赶走新来的那个呢
I thought you were getting rid of the new one here.

1020
00:59:59,850 --> 01:00:00,640
已经赶走了
And I've done it,

1021
01:00:00,640 --> 01:00:04,400
但我不确定卡森是否会让我接任
but I'm not sure Carson's going to let me take over.

1022
01:00:07,900 --> 01:00:10,070
我想跟你在一起
And I want to be with you.

1023
01:00:23,920 --> 01:00:26,790
我看不到咱俩的未来  你呢
I just can't see it working, can you?

1024
01:00:27,960 --> 01:00:29,390
我们之间似乎没有
We don't seem to have the basis

1025
01:00:29,390 --> 01:00:31,880
发展主仆恋情的可能  不是吗
of a servant-master relationship, do we?

1026
01:00:31,970 --> 01:00:33,800
你来此不就是为了与我相会
You came here to be with me.

1027
01:00:33,800 --> 01:00:35,470
还有别的目的
Among other reasons.

1028
01:00:38,930 --> 01:00:42,100
记住孤燕不成夏
And one swallow doesn't make a summer.

1029
01:00:58,160 --> 01:01:01,040
-你是不是忘了什么  -什么
- Aren't you forgetting something? - What?

1030
01:01:02,700 --> 01:01:05,210
你这是威胁我吗
Are you threatening me?

1031
01:01:08,340 --> 01:01:10,960
一段年少无知的风流韵事
Because of a youthful dalliance?

1032
01:01:11,050 --> 01:01:13,050
伦敦社交忙季的数周缱绻
A few weeks of madness in a London season?

1033
01:01:13,130 --> 01:01:14,970
你不会要拿这些事威胁我吧
You wouldn't hold that against me, surely?

1034
01:01:15,050 --> 01:01:17,010
困兽犹斗  何况是人
I would if I have to.

1035
01:01:22,180 --> 01:01:25,890
谁会相信一个贪婪男仆指证公爵的话
And who'd believe a greedy footman over the words of a duke?

1036
01:01:25,980 --> 01:01:29,360
你若不谨慎行事  小心牢狱之灾
If you're not careful, you'll end up behind bars.

1037
01:01:29,860 --> 01:01:31,610
我有证据
I've got proof.

1038
01:01:35,900 --> 01:01:37,610
你是指这些书信
You mean these?

1039
01:01:54,050 --> 01:01:56,010
我母亲一直叮嘱我
You know, my mother's always telling me

1040
01:01:56,010 --> 01:01:57,720
别留下白纸黑字的明证
never put anything in writing.

1041
01:01:57,800 --> 01:02:00,720
如今  多亏了你  我会引以为戒的
And now, thanks to you, I never will again.

1042
01:02:00,800 --> 01:02:02,260
你怎么拿到的
How did you get them?

1043
01:02:02,890 --> 01:02:03,900
你这个混蛋
You bastard.

1044
01:02:03,900 --> 01:02:06,060
别一失算就气急败坏  托马斯
Don't be a bad loser, Thomas.

1045
01:02:06,230 --> 01:02:07,730
睡觉去吧
Go to bed.

1046
01:02:09,100 --> 01:02:11,150
除非你想留下过夜
Unless you want to stay.

1047
01:02:44,100 --> 01:02:46,390
我要睡了
I think I'll turn in.

1048
01:02:46,480 --> 01:02:48,850
-没什么重要消息吗  -没有
- No big announcement, then? - No.

1049
01:02:48,940 --> 01:02:52,060
也不可能有了  他乘明早九点的火车离开
Nor likely to be. He's off on the 9:00 train.

1050
01:02:52,150 --> 01:02:53,610
他怎么能这样
He never is!

1051
01:02:53,690 --> 01:02:56,480
为了明日的晚宴  我们都宰好了一只火鸡呢
And when we've had a turkey killed for tomorrow's dinner!

1052
01:02:56,570 --> 01:02:59,820
-她到底做错了什么  -她没错
- I wonder what she did wrong. - She did nothing wrong.

1053
01:02:59,910 --> 01:03:02,780
听老爷那口气  她应该没错
Not from the way his lordship was talking.

1054
01:03:02,950 --> 01:03:06,040
真不知公爵大人的礼数教养都到哪里去了
So His Grace turned out to be graceless.

1055
01:03:08,120 --> 01:03:10,210
晚安  休斯太太
Good night, Mrs Hughes.

1056
01:03:10,290 --> 01:03:12,250
晚安  卡森先生
Good night, Mr Carson.

1057
01:03:15,710 --> 01:03:19,260
既然你意已决  何必让玛丽卷进来
If you knew that was your decision, why put Mary through it?

1058
01:03:19,340 --> 01:03:20,800
我之前还犹豫不决
But I didn't know it was my decision,

1059
01:03:20,810 --> 01:03:23,340
直到今晚  才最终决定
my final decision, until tonight.

1060
01:03:23,430 --> 01:03:25,550
我觉得  我不能为了玛丽
But I find I cannot ruin the estate

1061
01:03:25,550 --> 01:03:27,810
破坏这份家业  辱没这个头衔
or hollow out the title for the sake of Mary,

1062
01:03:27,890 --> 01:03:30,430
就算她嫁个更好的人也不行
even with a better man than that.

1063
01:03:30,520 --> 01:03:33,020
我无论如何也理解不了
I try to understand. I just can't.

1064
01:03:33,110 --> 01:03:36,150
不理解也罢  唐顿是我的家族祖业
Well, why should you? Downton is in my blood and in my bones.

1065
01:03:36,230 --> 01:03:37,860
又不是你的
It's not in yours.

1066
01:03:37,940 --> 01:03:39,990
我不能成为一个卖国贼
And I can no more be the cause of its destruction

1067
01:03:40,070 --> 01:03:42,150
也决不能成为败家子
than I could betray my country.

1068
01:03:42,240 --> 01:03:43,580
再说  之前我又不知道
Besides, how was I to know

1069
01:03:43,580 --> 01:03:45,070
他只是冲着整个家产来的
he wouldn't take her without the money?

1070
01:03:45,160 --> 01:03:47,490
别得了便宜还卖乖
Don't pretend to be a child because it suits you.

1071
01:03:47,580 --> 01:03:50,500
你觉得她跟慕钱而来的人结婚会幸福吗
Do you think she would've been happy with a fortune hunter?

1072
01:03:50,580 --> 01:03:52,370
也许会呢
She might've been.

1073
01:03:52,790 --> 01:03:54,000
我就很幸福
I was.

1074
01:03:57,210 --> 01:03:58,340
你真的幸福吗
Have you been happy?

1075
01:03:58,340 --> 01:04:01,170
我真让你觉得幸福吗
Really, have I made you happy?

1076
01:04:02,050 --> 01:04:03,630
真的
Yes.

1077
01:04:07,350 --> 01:04:09,540
你爱上我的那刻起  幸福就开始了
That is, since you fell in love with me,

1078
01:04:09,540 --> 01:04:10,730
如果我没记错的话
which, if I remember correctly,

1079
01:04:10,810 --> 01:04:13,310
大概是我们结婚一年后
was about a year after we were married.

1080
01:04:13,400 --> 01:04:16,310
没有一年  没那么长时间
Not a year. Not as long as that.

1081
01:04:16,860 --> 01:04:18,900
但这种好事不一定会落在玛丽身上
But it wouldn't have happened for Mary.

1082
01:04:18,900 --> 01:04:19,760
为什么
Why not?

1083
01:04:20,900 --> 01:04:24,910
我这人可比克罗伯勒公爵好多了
Because I am so much nicer than the Duke of Crowborough.

1084
01:04:25,530 --> 01:04:26,820
这得我说了算
I'll be the judge of that.

1085
01:04:30,790 --> 01:04:33,830
别以为我会袖手旁观  罗伯特
Just don't think I'm going to let it rest, Robert.

1086
01:04:33,920 --> 01:04:36,460
我不达目的  誓不罢休
I haven't given up by any means.

1087
01:04:38,250 --> 01:04:42,800
-我做事得对得起自己的良心  -我也是
- I must do what my conscience tells me. - And so must I.

1088
01:04:44,550 --> 01:04:47,930
还有  你别以为我会就此罢休
And I don't want you to think I'll let it rest.

1089
01:05:00,440 --> 01:05:02,740
老爷  可否让贝茨
My lord, would it be acceptable

1090
01:05:02,740 --> 01:05:05,030
与泰勒在前座将就下
for Bates to ride in front with Taylor?

1091
01:05:05,110 --> 01:05:07,320
否则就得另外备车了
Otherwise, it means getting the other car out.

1092
01:05:07,410 --> 01:05:09,830
他和公爵大人赶的是同一班火车
He and His Grace are catching the same train.

1093
01:05:09,910 --> 01:05:11,740
完全可以
Perfectly acceptable.

1094
01:05:11,830 --> 01:05:15,210
公爵大人就算不乐意  也只能将就下了
And if His Grace doesn't like it, he can lump it.

1095
01:05:28,760 --> 01:05:30,970
格兰瑟姆夫人  您实在太客气了  谢谢
You've been so kind, Lady Grantham. Thank you.

1096
01:05:31,060 --> 01:05:32,720
再见  公爵
Goodbye, Duke.

1097
01:05:33,060 --> 01:05:35,520
烦请您替我向令媛道个别
You'll make my farewells to your delightful daughters?

1098
01:05:35,600 --> 01:05:37,940
她们若知道您现在就走  定会亲自相送
They'd have been down if they'd known you were leaving so soon.

1099
01:05:38,020 --> 01:05:41,320
确实有突发急事  不得不走
Alas, something's come up which has taken me quite by surprise.

1100
01:05:41,400 --> 01:05:42,860
看得出来
Obviously.

1101
01:05:43,240 --> 01:05:46,110
格兰瑟姆  贵宅小住非常愉快
Well, Grantham, this has been a highly enjoyable interlude.

1102
01:05:46,200 --> 01:05:48,530
是吗  我还担心是否让您失望了
Has it? And I feared it had proved a disappointment.

1103
01:05:48,620 --> 01:05:49,820
怎么会  完全没有
Not at all, not at all.

1104
01:05:49,910 --> 01:05:52,370
小住一日  得知你们都好  我就安心多了
A short stay in your lovely house has driven away my cares.

1105
01:05:52,450 --> 01:05:56,410
老爷  要赶上这班火车的话  我们得走了
We ought to go, my lord, if His Grace is to catch the train.

1106
01:05:58,880 --> 01:06:01,340
再见  贝茨  祝你好运
Goodbye, Bates, and good luck.

1107
01:06:02,960 --> 01:06:05,090
也祝您好运  老爷
Good luck to you, my lord.

1108
01:06:23,650 --> 01:06:24,980
等等
Wait!

1109
01:06:27,950 --> 01:06:31,200
-贝茨  下车  -我真不能误了这班火车
- Get out, Bates. - I really mustn't be late.

1110
01:06:33,200 --> 01:06:36,500
回屋去  解雇的事绝不再提了
Get back inside and we'll say no more about it.

1111
01:06:51,550 --> 01:06:53,720
卡森  不该让他走
It wasn't right, Carson.

1112
01:06:54,390 --> 01:06:56,890
不该赶他走的
I just didn't think it was right.

1113
01:07:14,330 --> 01:07:17,080
-夫人  急件  -谢谢  艾伦
- First post, ma'am. - Thank you, Ellen.

1114
01:07:20,670 --> 01:07:23,580
-这封是你的  -谢谢  母亲
- One for you. - Thank you, Mother.

1115
01:07:34,010 --> 01:07:36,030
是格兰瑟姆伯爵寄来的
Oh, it's from Lord Grantham.

1116
01:07:36,030 --> 01:07:38,520
真的吗  他有什么事会找你
Really? What on earth does he want?

1117
01:07:41,350 --> 01:07:43,690
他想要改变我们的命运
He wants to change our lives.

